notesStmt.note: Repaired and infilled, partially laminated. All edges guarded before rebinding.
The leaf marked 1*** is a fragment cut out from folio 16 of the editio princeps of bYevamot (Venice, 1522).
Some other leaves prefixed to the original manuscript contain poetical compositions, currently mostly illegible.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 25; written lines: 25; Non-uniform layout. Original foliation. Some pages left blank. Lacunae after folios 10, 11, and other places.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental semi-cursive script of the 18th to 19th century.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'Religious Poetry. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 5470.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: S. Raffalovich: purchased by the British Museum on 13 December 1908: inscribed, folio [102v] (fse001v).
